This paper deals with the convergence analysis of stochastic $k$-means algorithm, which is a popular method for large-scale clustering and unsupervised feature learning. The paper uses ideas from recent work on stochastic gradient descent for non-convex problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization research (cs.LG). The paper also involves analysis of clustering algorithms and their convergence rates, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on clustering and unsupervised learning suggests that it could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
